16 "(a.1)(1) On and after January 1, 2024, the tax imposed pursuant to subsection (a) of this
17 Code section shall be 5.39 percent for taxable years beginning on or after
18 January 1, 2024; provided, however, that such rate shall be reduced by 0.10 percent
19 annually beginning on January 1, 2025, until the rate reaches 4.99 3.99 percent, provided
20 such annual reductions in the tax rate shall be subject to delays as provided in
21 paragraph (2) of this subsection.
22 (2) Each prospective annual reduction in the tax rate that would otherwise occur as
23 provided in paragraph (1) of this subsection shall be delayed by one year for each year
24 that any of the following are true as of December 1:
25 (A) The Governor's revenue estimate for the succeeding fiscal year is not at least 3
26 percent above the Governor's revenue estimate for the present fiscal year;
27 (B) The prior fiscal year's net revenue collection was not higher than each of the
28 preceding three fiscal years' net tax revenue collection; or
29 (C) The Revenue Shortfall Reserve provided for in Code Section 45-12-93 does not
30 contain a sum that exceeds the amount of the decrease in state revenue projected to
31 occur as a result of the prospective reduction in the tax rates set to occur the following
32 year.
33 (3) The Office of Planning and Budget shall make the determinations necessary to
34 implement the provisions of paragraph (2) of this subsection and shall report its
35 determinations by December 1 of each year to the department, the Speaker of the House
36 of Representatives, the President of the Senate, and the chairpersons of the House
37 Appropriations Committee, the House Ways and Means Committee, the Senate
38 Appropriations Committee, and the Senate Finance Committee. This paragraph shall not
39 be applicable after the final reduction to the rate of 4.99 3.99 percent occurs."
