40 SECTION 2.
41 Part 1 of Article 4 of Chapter 12 of Title 45 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
42 relating to management of budgetary and financial affairs, is amended by revising Code
43 Section 45-12-93, relating to revenue shortfall reserve, reservation of surplus state funds,
44 appropriation and release of funds, and limitations, as follows:
45 "45-12-93.
46 (a) There shall be a reserve of state funds known as the 'Revenue Shortfall Reserve.'
47 (b) The amount of all surplus in state funds existing as of the end of each fiscal year shall
48 be reserved and added to the Revenue Shortfall Reserve. Funds in the Revenue Shortfall
49 Reserve shall carry forward from fiscal year to fiscal year, without reverting to the general
50 fund at the end of a fiscal year. The Revenue Shortfall Reserve shall be maintained,
51 accumulated, appropriated, and otherwise disbursed only as provided in this Code section.
52 (c) For each existing fiscal year, the General Assembly may appropriate from the Revenue
53 Shortfall Reserve an amount up to 1 percent of the net revenue collections of the preceding
54 fiscal year for funding increased K-12 needs.
55 (d) The Governor may release for appropriation by the General Assembly a stated amount
56 from funds in the Revenue Shortfall Reserve that are in excess of 4 percent of the net
57 revenue of the preceding fiscal year.
58 (e) As of the end of each fiscal year, an amount shall be released from the Revenue
59 Shortfall Reserve to the general fund to cover any deficit by which total expenditures and
60 contractual obligations of state funds authorized by appropriation exceed net revenue and
61 other amounts in state funds made available for appropriation.
62 (f) The combined Revenue Shortfall Reserve and the Midyear Adjustment Reserve
63 existing on May 9, 2005, shall become the Revenue Shortfall Reserve provided for in this
64 Code section. Any amount of the Revenue Shortfall Reserve exceeding 25 percent of the
65 previous fiscal year's net revenue may be used for tax relief pursuant to Acts of the General
66 Assembly.
